# Google Place photos — image widget rule

- For **`Place.photos`**, Moody **`photo_url`**, or any Google place image URL from Explore / `places_cache` / My Day / planner activities, use **`WmPlacePhotoNetworkImage`** (`lib/core/presentation/widgets/wm_network_image.dart`). That includes:
  - Legacy: `maps.googleapis.com/.../place/photo?photoreference=...`
  - Places API (New): `places.googleapis.com/v1/.../photos/.../media?...` (Moody `searchPlacesV1` / `transformPlaceV1`)
  Same pipeline everywhere (hero, list cards, grid, mood carousels, trending, Foto’s, fullscreen).
- **`deviceAccessibleGooglePlacePhotoUrl`** (`lib/core/utils/google_place_photo_device_url.dart`) rewrites the **`key=`** query param for both shapes above so the device uses **`ApiKeys.googlePlacesKey`**; do not reimplement that per screen.
- For avatars, Unsplash, social images, or other non–place-photo HTTPS URLs: use **`WmNetworkImage`**.
- Do not use raw `Image.network` or plain **`CachedNetworkImage`** without the rewriter for Google place photos. Do not duplicate URL rewriting outside **`deviceAccessibleGooglePlacePhotoUrl`** / **`WmPlacePhotoNetworkImage`**.
